# Cost-Accounted Rho Calculus — Formal Verification
#
# Proves that cost accounting (phlogiston) can be faithfully encoded back
# into pure rho calculus via a compositional translation, making cost
# control a first-class citizen of computation.
#
# Source: cost-accounted-rho.pdf (Meredith)
# Companion doc: docs/theory/cost-accounted-rho-verification.md
#
# 32 modules with kernel-checked theorem bodies. The development is
# parameterized over a single
# hash_process function and 3 structural/cryptographic hypotheses on
# it; all consensus-critical results (ca_cost_deterministic,
# ca_step_deterministic, token_monotone_*, fuel_events_consumed_perm)
# are unconditional (see verification doc §11.1). Replication encoding
# is scoped to the axiom-free forward weak-barb propagation theorem
# [preplicate_bang_encoding_body_barbs_sound].
#
# Module dependency graph (→ = "depends on"):
#
#   RhoSyntax                   (standalone)
#   StructEquivInversion        → RhoSyntax
#   StructEquivHeads            → RhoSyntax, StructEquivInversion
#   RhoReduction                → RhoSyntax, StructEquivInversion, StructEquivHeads
#   CostAccountedSyntax         → RhoSyntax
#   CostAccountedReduction      → CostAccountedSyntax, RhoSyntax
#   Translation                 → RhoSyntax, StructEquivInversion, StructEquivHeads,
#                                 RhoReduction, CostAccountedSyntax
#   ChannelSeparation           → RhoSyntax, CostAccountedSyntax, Translation
#   TokenConservation           → CostAccountedSyntax, CostAccountedReduction
#   Settlement                  → TokenConservation
#   SlashingComposition         → Settlement
#   MergeableChannelAccounting  → Settlement
#   RuntimeBudgetRefinement     → CostAccountedSyntax
#   FuelEventDecomposition      → CostAccountedSyntax, CostAccountedReduction
#   StrongNormalization         → CostAccountedReduction, TokenConservation
#   Confluence                  → CostAccountedReduction, StrongNormalization
#   StepDeterminism             → CostAccountedReduction, Confluence
#   TranslationFaithfulness     → Translation, ChannelSeparation, RhoReduction,
#                                 CostAccountedReduction, TokenConservation;
#                                 includes recursive metered reflection
#   FuelGateSafety              → RhoSyntax, RhoReduction, Translation,
#                                 CostAccountedSyntax, ChannelSeparation
#   Bisimulation                → RhoSyntax, RhoReduction, Translation,
#                                 TranslationFaithfulness
#   Replication                 → RhoSyntax, StructEquivInversion,
#                                 StructEquivHeads, RhoReduction, Bisimulation
#   WeakBarbedEquiv             → RhoReduction
#   LinearLogicResources        → CostAccountedSyntax
#   LLIdentities                → (standalone; Stdlib only)
#   WalletNaming                → RhoSyntax
#   MintingInjection            → TokenConservation, WalletNaming
#   MintingHalt                 → MintingInjection
#   Exchange                    → TokenConservation, MintingInjection
#   SystemStructEquiv           → RhoSyntax, CostAccountedSyntax
#   SyntacticSugar              → Translation
#   MultiSignerRefinement       → RuntimeBudgetRefinement
#   UseCaseAdequacy             → TokenConservation, Settlement,
#                                 SlashingComposition, MergeableChannelAccounting,
#                                 RuntimeBudgetRefinement,
#                                 FuelEventDecomposition, Confluence,
#                                 StepDeterminism, TranslationFaithfulness
#
# Critical path: RhoSyntax → RhoReduction → Translation
#              → TranslationFaithfulness → Bisimulation
# Cost-determinism stack: TokenConservation → StrongNormalization
#              → Confluence → StepDeterminism
# Settlement stack: TokenConservation → Settlement →
#              SlashingComposition / MergeableChannelAccounting
# Runtime refinement stack: CostAccountedSyntax → RuntimeBudgetRefinement

-Q theories CostAccountedRho

# Level 0: Foundation (no dependencies)
theories/RhoSyntax.v

# Level 0b: Structural equivalence inversion (depends on RhoSyntax only)
theories/StructEquivInversion.v

# Level 0c: Heads-list permutation machinery (depends on StructEquivInversion)
theories/StructEquivHeads.v

# Level 1: Operational semantics (depend on RhoSyntax + inversion machinery)
theories/RhoReduction.v
theories/CostAccountedSyntax.v

# Level 2: Cost-accounted reduction (depends on Level 0-1)
theories/CostAccountedReduction.v

# Level 3: Translation (depends on Levels 0-2)
theories/Translation.v

# Level 3b: Channel separation (depends on RhoSyntax, CostAccountedSyntax)
theories/ChannelSeparation.v

# Level 4: Token conservation (depends on CostAccountedReduction)
theories/TokenConservation.v

# Level 4a0: Minting-injection layering theorem (depends on TokenConservation
# and WalletNaming). Proves minting is exogenous token injection, never a
# cost-accounted step (so conservation/SN/confluence survive verbatim), and —
# Stage B — the supply-pool balance layer: Σ⟦v⟧ injectivity in pk, epoch-mint
# idempotency on the balance, and user steps never move a supply balance.
theories/MintingInjection.v

# Level 4a: Post-evaluation fee settlement (depends on TokenConservation)
theories/Settlement.v

# Level 4a2: Slashing composition boundary (depends on Settlement)
theories/SlashingComposition.v

# Level 4a3: Typed mergeable-channel accounting boundary (depends on Settlement)
theories/MergeableChannelAccounting.v

# Level 4a4: Bounded-memory runtime-budget refinement (depends on syntax)
theories/RuntimeBudgetRefinement.v

# Level 4b: Fuel event decomposition (depends on CostAccountedReduction)
theories/FuelEventDecomposition.v

# Level 4c: Strong normalization (depends on TokenConservation)
theories/StrongNormalization.v

# Level 4d: Confluence and cost determinism (depends on StrongNormalization,
# CostAccountedReduction)
theories/Confluence.v

# Level 4e: Step determinism for single-token systems (depends on Confluence)
theories/StepDeterminism.v

# Level 5: Main faithfulness theorem (depends on TokenConservation for the
# PR #466 immunity corollary)
theories/TranslationFaithfulness.v

# Level 5: Other main theorems (depend on Translation; can be developed in parallel)
theories/FuelGateSafety.v

# Level 6: Bisimulation (depends on TranslationFaithfulness for compound
# helpers compound_outer_gate_fires_closed, compound_inner_gate_fires_closed,
# and compound_half_fires_two_step used in the SAnd compound bisim case)
theories/Bisimulation.v

# Level 6b: Weak barbs (coinduction-free, depends only on RhoReduction's
# split-barb infrastructure). Provides the framework used by
# Replication.v for the body-to-wrapper barb propagation theorem.
theories/WeakBarbedEquiv.v

# Level 7: Meredith's reflection-based replication encoding. Mechanizes
# the one-step unfolding and forward weak-barb propagation facts used by
# the verification record.
theories/Replication.v

# Level 4a5: Phase 1.10 multi-signature refinement (depends on
# RuntimeBudgetRefinement; Qed-closed Map-in-MVar PoS-refinement +
# FIFO drain conservation theorems).
theories/MultiSignerRefinement.v

# Level 4a6: Publication-derived linear-resource calculus (depends on
# CostAccountedSyntax). Mechanizes the mixed unrestricted/linear resource
# boundary, anti-contraction/anti-weakening, no-double-spend, and runtime
# sig_algebra bridge.
theories/LinearLogicResources.v

# Level 4a7: Phase 2/3 linear-logic identities (standalone; depends only
# on Stdlib). Mechanizes canonical multiplicative / additive / exponential
# laws + Phase 2 Threshold permutation invariance.
theories/LLIdentities.v

# Level 3c: System-level structural equivalence + source-level free names
# (depends on RhoSyntax, CostAccountedSyntax). Mechanizes the commutative-
# monoid sys_equiv (parallel-unit law sse_par_unit, Appendix-B token_decomp)
# and the FN_s(#P)=FN(P) free-name bridge (Def 3.3 g/#P axes; §3.5).
theories/SystemStructEquiv.v

# Level 3d: Section 3.8 syntactic sugar at the translation level (depends on
# Translation). Mechanizes the uniform-signing and linear-transfer (⊸) sugar
# defining equations as proc-level structural equivalences of the translated
# images (option A; ⊸ desugars to nested plain-signature gate layers).
theories/SyntacticSugar.v

# Level 8: Use-case adequacy corollaries over the proof stack.
theories/UseCaseAdequacy.v

# Level 0d: Per-validator wallet @W_v naming (Cost-Accounted Rho Stage A;
# DR-13). Depends only on RhoSyntax. Proves wallet-name injectivity in the
# validator public key (distinct validators ⇒ distinct draw wallets) and
# pairwise disjointness of the wallet / quarantine / funding-slot seed
# DOMAINS. Axiom- and hypothesis-free (concrete injective bit-encoder), so
# its headline theorems are Closed under the global context.
theories/WalletNaming.v

# Level 4a1: Stage-C halt INTERFACE proved at Stage B (DR-3 / DR-13). Depends
# on MintingInjection (the PoS-state / epoch-mint abstraction) — INDEPENDENT of
# MainTheorem.v / the slashing tree (G-coordination). Proves a halted validator
# is never minted and never gains supply, and that redemption (clearing the
# halt) is the only way a halted validator regains supply. Concrete, so its
# headline theorems are Closed under the global context.
theories/MintingHalt.v

# Level 4a8: Stage-D blessed Exchange — the conserving 1:1 token swap (spec
# "Fee conversion" tex:3061-3084 / DR-4). Depends on TokenConservation +
# MintingInjection. Proves per-channel + total conservation of the swap, the
# DR-4 requires-both-inputs join property, and that Exchange is a cost-accounted
# step (fuel-non-increasing) never an exogenous mint. Concrete, so its headline
# theorems are Closed under the global context.
theories/Exchange.v

# GSLT/OSLF capstone — discharges spec §6.1 (the calculus is a well-formed
# GSLT: Types / Equations / Rewrites) and §7.7 (the OSLF-generated linear
# resource logic: the funding judgment Σ_s ≥ Δ_s is decidable, the gate is a
# sound proof-checker, an underfunded deploy is rejected, and the logic is
# linear / no-contraction). Assembles already-proven Qed-closed results;
# framework-independent (no MeTTaIL). Closed under the global context.
theories/GSLTOSLFCapstone.v

# Rule-4/5 continuation re-seal adequacy (GAP-2 / #7). Depends on RhoSyntax +
# CostAccountedSyntax. Proves the Rocq model's re-seal of the bare-proc Rule-4/5
# continuation under SAnd(s1,s2) is COST-BENIGN: a seal carries no fuel
# (system_token_count (SSigned _ _) = 0), so the token count — the cost the cost
# theorems and consensus meter — is independent of the continuation's seal, hence
# identical to the spec's receiver seal s1. Axiom-free; Closed under the global
# context.
theories/Rule45ContinuationAdequacy.v
